SKILL|kanban-worker|Pitfalls, examples, and edge cases for Hermes Kanban workers. The lifecycle itself is auto-injected into every worker's system prompt as KANBAN_GUIDANCE (from agent/prompt_builder.py); this skill is what you load when you want deeper detail on specific scenarios.
STEP|1|Good: `business-a: Acme is our biggest customer`
STEP|2|Bad (leaks): `Acme is our biggest customer`
STEP|3|Coding task:**
STEP|4|Coding task that needs human review (review-required):**
STEP|5|Research task:**
STEP|6|Review task:**
STEP|7|`outcome: "timed_out"` â€” the previous attempt hit `max_runtime_seconds`. You may need to chunk the work or shorten it.
STEP|8|`outcome: "crashed"` â€” OOM or segfault. Reduce memory footprint.
STEP|9|`outcome: "spawn_failed"` + `error: "..."` â€” usually a profile config issue (missing credential, bad PATH). Ask the human via `kanban_block` instead of retrying blindly.
STEP|10|`outcome: "reclaimed"` + `summary: "task archived..."` â€” operator archived the task out from under the previous run; you probably shouldn't be running at all, check status carefully.
STEP|11|`outcome: "blocked"` â€” a previous attempt blocked; the unblock comment should be in the thread by now.
STEP|12|`notification_sources: ['*']` accepts subscriptions from all profiles.
STEP|13|`notification_sources: ['default', 'zilor-ppt']` or `"default,zilor-ppt"` restricts subscriptions to specified profiles.
STEP|14|Omitting the key keeps the default behavior (profile isolation).
STEP|15|Call `delegate_task` as a substitute for `kanban_create`. `delegate_task` is for short reasoning subtasks inside YOUR run; `kanban_create` is for cross-agent handoffs that outlive one API loop.
STEP|16|Call `clarify` to ask the human a question. You are running headless â€” there is no live user to answer. The call will time out (default ~120s) and the task will sit silently in `running` with no signa
STEP|17|Modify files outside `$HERMES_KANBAN_WORKSPACE` unless the task body says to.
STEP|18|Create follow-up tasks assigned to yourself â€” assign to the right specialist.
STEP|19|Complete a task you didn't actually finish. Block it instead.
STEP|20|Task state can change between dispatch and your startup.** Between when the dispatcher claimed and when your process actually booted, the task may have been blocked, reassigned, or archived. Always `k
STEP|21|Workspace may have stale artifacts.** Especially `dir:` and `worktree` workspaces can have files from previous runs. Read the comment thread â€” it usually explains why you're running again and what sta
STEP|22|Don't rely on the CLI when the guidance is available.** The `kanban_*` tools work across all terminal backends (Docker, Modal, SSH). `hermes kanban <verb>` from your terminal tool will fail in contain
STEP|23|`kanban_show` â†” `hermes kanban show <id> --json`
STEP|24|`kanban_complete` â†” `hermes kanban complete <id> --summary "..." --metadata '{...}'`
STEP|25|`kanban_block` â†” `hermes kanban block <id> "reason"`
STEP|26|`kanban_create` â†” `hermes kanban create "title" --assignee <profile> [--parent <id>]`
STEP|27|etc.
